headline: 3 Reasons to Sell TER and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: The past six months have been a windfall for Teradyne’s shareholders. The company’s stock price has jumped 121%, hitting $190.68 per share. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
